    "summary": "I am an independent scholar, adventurer and entrepreneur:\n- studied Slavic languages,\n- studied Turkic languages\n- studied Koranic and Classical Arabic as well as various dialects,\n- travelled extensively with a focus on the areas whose languages I was learning such as the Balkans, Turkey and the Arab world, but also North America as far as Nome, Alaska,\n- drove both Amsterdam city buses and  European long-distance coaches, \n- drove international long-haul trucks in Europe and the Middle East, \n- served in the Army as a peace keeper in a war zone, \n- set up a company of inventors and designers,\n- invented smart font technology together with my partners;\n- made computer models (\"fonts\") of previously unreproducible  Arabic scripts; \n- contribute regularly to Unicode and typography conferences,\n- contribute regularly to the World Public Forum on Rhodes, \n- contributed to the emerging text critical analysis of the Koran on several Corpus Coranicum conferences in Berlin, \n- am a member of the Inarah Institute for Research on Early Islam and Koran in Saarbruecken, Germany, \n- co-authored with Eildert Mulder a critical analysis of Western Islam studies (De omstreden bronnen van de Islam - the debatable origins of Islam),\n- published many articles on the structure and history of Arabic script. \n- wrote a number of newspaper articles and op-eds in the Dutch (Trouw, Volkskrant, NRC) and international press (Christian Science Monitor, Jordan Times, as-Sayad Magazine Lebanon) about Middle Eastern politics\n\nSpecialties: Writing systems, multi-lingual typography, Arabic-scripted typography; early Islam, Global Computing",
