                    "company": "Brill",
                    "description": "\"Thomas Milo\u2019s Qur\u02be\u0101n Concordance Online (QCO) is a finding aid designed for scholars and students of the Qur\u02be\u0101n. The Q-Concordance is the result of original research on the earliest known (fragments of) Qur\u02be\u0101n manuscripts, as well as various printed editions. By comparing these texts word for word, Milo has identified all common denominators. \nBecause the earliest manuscripts often do not contain all the diacritics of the Arabic script, Milo has devised a \u201ccode\u201d to represent the handwritten texts in the most faithful way possible. This representation of the text allows researchers to find all possible interpretations of a given word found in the handwritten texts.\nThe search results are represented side by side with a digital version of the 1924 Cairo edition of the Qur\u02be\u0101n to facilitate comparison. The Cairo edition\u2019s original text in Arabic orthography has been preserved in its exact layout of 827 pages, because in this edition every word has a fixed position on the page. In split-screen the Q-Concordance presents both the digital Cairo edition (on the left) and Milo\u2019s coded representation (on the right), allowing the user easily to connect search results from the code with specific locations in the edition.\n\nThomas Milo\u2019s Q-Concordance is the only research tool designed especially to reflect both the manuscript and print traditions of the Quranic text. It is an indispensable finding aid for scholars and students of the Qur\u02be\u0101n, and for everyone working with early Islamic Arabic (epigraphic, papyrus, numismatic, etc.) texts.\"\n(From Brill's product description)\n\nNow online:\nhttp://referenceworks.brillonline.com/cluster/Encyclopaedia%20of%20the%20Qur%CA%BE%C4%81n?s.num=0",
                    "title": "Author of and Licensor to Brill of the New Concordance to the Qur\u02be\u0101n",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
